  "content": "\nThen: `cd /root/corvia-project/corvia-workspace/repos/corvia && cargo test --workspace`\nExpected: All tests pass.\n\n**Step 8: Commit**\n\n```bash\ngit add -A && git commit -m \"feat(m3.4): integrate RustModuleMap into AstChunker and treesitter (D72)\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Add `pulldown-cmark` and extract markdown cross-references\n\n**Files:**\n- Modify: `corvia-kernel/Cargo.toml`\n- Modify: `corvia-kernel/src/chunking_markdown.rs`\n\n**Step 1: Add `pulldown-cmark` dependency**\n\nIn `crates/corvia-kernel/Cargo.toml` under `[dependencies]`, add:\n```toml\npulldown-cmark = \"0.12\"\n```\n\n**Step 2: Add relation extraction to `MarkdownChunker::chunk()`**\n\nIn `crates/corvia-kernel/src/chunking_markdown.rs`, add these imports at the top:\n```rust\nuse crate::chunking_strategy::ChunkRelation;\n```\n\nAdd a helper method to `MarkdownChunker`:\n```rust\nimpl MarkdownChunker {\n    // ... existing methods ...\n\n    /// Extract cross-references from markdown content using pulldown-cmark.\n    ///\n    /// Finds:\n    /// - Code spans with CamelCase identifiers (likely types/traits)\n    /// - Links to file paths with known extensions\n    /// - File paths referenced in fenced code blocks\n    fn extract_references(\n        source: &str,",
